-- Mexico Stocks: Ica, OHL Mexico, Minera Frisco Shares Gain
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-07T23:08:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/mexico-stocks-ica-ohl-mexico-minera-frisco-shares-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC index rose 0.2 percent to 37,548.54.  Homebuilders and construction-related companies led gains,
reversing their slump yesterday, after a Wall Street Journal
report that the Federal Reserve is discussing a new type of
bond-buying program.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s biggest
construction company, jumped 4.6 percent to 23.39 pesos.  Urbi
Desarrollos Urbanos (URBI*)  SAB, Mexico’s third-largest
homebuilder by sales, gained 1.9 percent to 14.37 pesos. OHL
Mexico SAB (OHLMEX* MM), the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL) , rose 2 percent to
21.95 pesos.  Minera Frisco SAB (MFRISCOA MM), the mining company
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , rose 3.3 percent to 56.44
pesos. Silver futures gained today in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
